Content:: One-day races and Classics Christopher Juul-Jensen (born 6 July 1989) is a Danish racing cyclist,[5] who currently rides for UCI WorldTeam Team BikeExchange–Jayco.[6] Juul-Jensen grew up in Ireland, living in County Wicklow until the age of 16.[7] He became the Danish national time trial champion in 2015. In August 2015 Orica–GreenEDGE announced that they had signed Juul-Jensen on an initial two-year contract from 2016.[8] He was named in the start list for the 2016 Tour de France.[9] Media related to Christopher Juul Jensen at Wikimedia Commons
